aPlusContent.title: Product Description
aPlusContent.rawText:
Product Description
National Geographic 75-Piece Magnetic Marble Run Construction Kit 
The video showcases the product in use.The video guides you through product setup.The video compares multiple products.The video shows the product being unpacked.
This wildly creative super puzzle includes 42 tracks & connectors, 17 trick pieces & 15 marbles for infinite combinations and endless amounts of dynamic fun! This one-of-a-kind marble maze can be built on any vertical magnetic surface like the fridge, lockers, whiteboards, workbenches & more! 
Brings a new level of excitement to building a marble maze! 
With its innovative magnetic connectors, kids and adults alike can build, create, and explore engineering and physics on any magnetic surface. 
This STEM marble run set provides everything you need: 28 magnetic connectors; 14 track pieces; 17 trick pieces - 2 funnels, 1 around, 2 flex, 2 poles, 2 simple spinners, 1 spinner pro, 1 bell, 1 switch, 1 catapult, 4 U-turns; 15 marbles; storage bag; detailed instructions, and fact-filled Learning Guide. 
Explore physics and engineering with the different types of track and trick pieces, creating astonishing chain reactions and intricate paths for your marbles. First, select a combination of track, trick, and connector pieces and arrange them creatively on any vertical magnetic surface. Place a marble at the beginning of the course and watch it make its way down your track. As you experiment and create, simply move the pieces around to make adjustments, add new pathways, or build new obstacles. Each track and trick has its own unique properties, but how to set them up is completely up to you‚Äîthe possibilities are endless! 
The National Geographic Magnetic Marble Run isn't your ordinary marble maze. From the kitchen to the office, it's an engineering kit with a Rube Goldberg machine-style of play that's super fun and satisfying. It‚Äôs also a fun, collaborative way to connect with family, friends and co-workers! The magnetic connectors work in tandem with the included track and trick pieces for endless marble run combinations and maze-like experiments on any magnetic surface. The connectors are sturdy yet easy to move around as you build and fine-tune your track. Its unique design also means less clutter on the floor, with a handy, durable storage bag to keep all your pieces and marbles safe and secure. 
And like all National Geographic STEM kits, the 75-Piece Magnetic Marble Run includes a detailed, illustrated Learning Guide to teach the science behind all the fun. Learn how to think like an engineer with an understanding of Newton's laws of motion, gravity, energy and more! 
Order the National Geographic 75-Piece Magnetic Marble Run today, and experience the non-stop fun of this one-of-a-kind STEM building set! 
We make the highest quality hands-on science toys, and all products are backed by exceptional service. With a mission to inspire people to care about the planet, the National Geographic Society is one of the world's largest nonprofit scientific and educational organizations.

Of course they do - they're Elites, endowed at birth with the most advanced genetic enhancements available. Elites are the pinnacle of evolution; the triumph of man's ambitions. The only problem in their perfect world are the humans! And their toys!
Now comes the most unbelievable shock of Hays Baker's life. Suddenly he's on the other side of the gun, experiencing a life he'd never dreamed possible - and fighting to save humans everywhere from extinction. And not only that. Hays and Lizbeth just might lose their perfect family.
James Patterson's Toys is a thriller on a hyper plane, with a hero to rival both Bond and Jason Bourne.

Product Description
Can you use real money to play? 
No, you can‚Äôt. The machine comes with plastic coins. Do not put game coins or small objects into the doll machine. 
Why doesn‚Äôt the claw machine work when the coin is placed in the slot? 
If the coin goes in too slowly, the machine may not start. Just insert another coin to start the machine. 
Does the machine need batteries? 
Yes, it needs 3 D batteries, which are not included. Alternatively, you can use a USB cable with a voltage lower than 5.5V. 
Why did the machine suddenly stop working? 
Maybe your hand or something was placed at the port, causing the machine to stop working. Or maybe the game time is up. Try inserting another coin to start the machine again. 
Can I keep playing by inserting a coin? 
The maximum time of each game is 60 seconds. when the time is up or a prize is successfully captured, the game will be terminated automatically. Need to re-coin to continue.
